<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/23651348-chris-hinkle"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_100x100-c7bfe730633c9983e27caaa66a8e244a.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23651348-chris-hinkle">Chris Hinkle</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It seems clear to me that Louise Penny is letting the readers believe (with Clara and Gamache) that if they didn&apos;t actually meet God, then something p<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It seems clear to me that Louise Penny is letting the readers believe (with Clara and Gamache) that if they didn't actually meet God, then something pretty close to that happened. El's knowledge of what Clara needed to hear, like the lemon pie, confirms the presence of grace.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
