<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1054609-is-the-whole-thing-with-agent-nicole">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Is the whole thing with Agent Nicole deliberately vague at the end? We're not supposed to know yet who she spoke to and what she set in motion (except vaguely to take Gamache down), right? And then he sets something in motion but we don't know what? It's the only part I found aggravating. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
